race.comment: NEVERMISTA (8) made a bold return at Muswellbrook when fighting gamely in the lane to just miss. Sure to have come on with that run under his belt and rates a leading player. MAGNOLIA JEWEL (13) showed early pace and fought hard to land the prize and shed her maiden tag at Coffs Harbour. Gets in light with the rise in grade and is a big chance to go on with it. HARD TOO IMPRESS (3) ran well two starts ago before a plain effort at Mudgee. Better suited this company and capable of bouncing back strongly. Just needs some luck from the wide draw. JOY OF THE WORLD (4) was solid first-up at Bathurst and will strip fitter. Gives herself every chance up on speed, so don't write her off. MISS KARIS (7) is edging closer and with Gallagher booked is one to consider.
